PROGRAM 4

Amazon S3 Bucket Operations

Aim
To create bucket upload object make object public and delete object.

Step 1 Open AWS Console

1. Open browser.
2. Login to AWS Skill Builder.
3. Open the S3 Lab.
4. On top right corner click Start Lab.
5. Wait until lab becomes green.
6. Click Open Console.
7. AWS Console opens in new tab.

Do not change AWS Region.

Step 2 Open S3 Service
Location
Top search bar of AWS Console.

1. Move to top side of AWS Console.
2. Click inside Search bar.
3. Type S3.
4. Under Services click S3.
5. Amazon S3 Dashboard opens.

Step 3 Create Bucket
Location
Center right side of S3 dashboard.

1. Locate orange Create bucket button.
2. Click Create bucket.

Step 4 Enter Bucket Details
Location
Top middle section called General Configuration.

1. Click inside Bucket name field.
2. Enter reportbucket123456.
3. Use random numbers at end for unique bucket name.

Example
reportbucket987987

Step 5 Configure Object Ownership
Scroll slightly down.

1. Find section Object Ownership.
2. Select ACLs enabled.
3. Select Object writer.

Step 6 Keep Default Settings

1. Do not change Region.
2. Do not change Encryption.
3. Keep all remaining settings default.

Step 7 Create Bucket
Location
Bottom right corner of page.

1. Scroll fully down.
2. Locate orange Create bucket button.
3. Click Create bucket.
4. Wait for success message.

Bucket is created successfully.

Step 8 Open Bucket
Location
Bucket list page.

1. Locate bucket name starting with reportbucket.
2. Click bucket name.
3. Bucket overview page opens.

Step 9 Upload File
Location
Top right side inside bucket.

1. Click Upload.
2. Upload wizard opens.

Step 10 Add File
Location
Middle section of upload page.

1. Click Add files.
2. File Explorer opens.
3. Select new report.png file.
4. Click Open.

Step 11 Upload Object

1. Scroll down to bottom.
2. Click Upload button.
3. Wait until upload reaches 100 percent.
4. Success message appears.

Step 12 Close Upload Status
Location
Top right of upload status page.

1. Click Close.
2. Uploaded file appears in Objects section.

Step 13 Open Uploaded Object
Location
Objects tab.

1. Locate new report.png.
2. Click file name.
3. Object Overview page opens.

Step 14 Copy Object URL
Scroll slightly down.

1. Find Object URL section.
2. Copy complete URL.

Step 15 Test Object URL

1. Open new browser tab.
2. Paste Object URL.
3. Press Enter.
4. Access Denied message appears.

Reason
Objects are private by default.

Step 16 Make Object Public

1. Return to AWS S3 tab.
2. Stay on Object Overview page.

Location
Top right side.

3. Click Object actions.
4. Dropdown menu opens.
5. Scroll inside dropdown if necessary.
6. Click Make public using ACL.
7. Confirm popup if it appears.

Object becomes public.

Step 17 Verify Public Access

1. Return to browser tab containing URL.
2. Refresh page.
3. File opens successfully.

Step 18 Delete Object

1. Return to bucket page.
2. Select checkbox beside uploaded file.

Location
Top right side.

3. Click Delete.
4. Type permanently delete.
5. Click Delete objects.

Object gets deleted.

Step 19 Delete Bucket

1. Click Buckets from left panel.
2. Select checkbox beside bucket name.

Location
Top right side.

3. Click Delete.
4. Enter bucket name for confirmation.
5. Click Delete bucket.

Bucket deleted successfully.

Result
Amazon S3 bucket operations completed successfully.

